Title : El Vol del Pollastre
Text : [[File:El Vol del Pollastre.jpg|thumb|Logo of the company]]
'''El Vol del Pollastre''' is a performing arts company based in [[Banyoles]], [[Pla de l'Estany]], founded in December 2009.<ref>{{cite book |author= Joan Olivas |author2= Miquel Torrent |editor= Ajuntament de Banyoles |title= El Teatre a Banyoles: dels inicis fins al 2005 |year= 2011 |isbn= 9788487257278|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CjniXwAACAAJ|language=catalan}}</ref><ref name="Dossier">{{cite web |url=http://premsa.gencat.cat/pres_fsvp/docs/2012/12/10/12/32/a7386dd9-de70-4379-b82a-585b539e294d.pdf |title=Press booklet for "Júlia?" |editor=Generalitat de Catalunya|language=catalan}}</ref><ref name="Dossier de Premsa de “De petits tots matàvem formigues”">{{cite web |url=http://elvoldelpollastre.com/Dossier%20de%20premsa%20%22De%20petits%20tots%20mat%C3%A0vem%20formigues.pdf |title=Press booklet for "De petits tots matàvem formigues" |editor=El Vol del Pollastre|language=catalan}}</ref> They have been responsible for the promotion of Banyoles carnival in the years 2010,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.diaridegirona.cat/comarques/2010/02/04/banyoles-presenta-cartell-del-carnaval-daquest-any/385546.html |title=Banyoles presenta el cartell del carnaval d'aquest any |language=catalan|editor=Diari de Girona |date= 4 February 2010}}</ref> 2011,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://banyoles.cat/controller.php?p_action=show_page&pagina_id=6&inst_id=403026 |title=Amb el Banyoliwood arriba el Carnestoltes de Banyoles 2011 |language=catalan|editor=Ajuntament de Banyoles |date= 17 February 2011}}</ref> 2012<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eixdigital.cat/Girona/Fires%20i%20festes/1156-lolimpic-games-of-banyoles-en-el-cap-de-setmana-de-carnestoltes.html |title=L'Olímpic Games of Banyoles en el cap de setmana de Carnestoltes |language=catalan |editor=Eix Digital |date= 1 February 2012}}</ref> and 2013,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.regio7.cat/especials/carnestoltes/2013/01/banyoles-presenta-carnestoltes-centrat-voltant-dels-ovnis-n151_15_3054.html |title=Banyoles presenta un carnestoltes centrat al voltant dels ovnis |language=catalan |editor=Regió7 |date= 29 January 2013}}</ref> the fourth edition of ''Fira del Món del Foc'' held in Banyoles in 2014,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ara.cat/comarquesgironines/Banyoles-capital-del-foc-polvora_0_1168683126.html |title=Banyoles, capital del foc i de la pólvora |publisher=[[Diari Ara]] |date= 15 July 2014|language=catalan}}</ref> as well as other small performances linked with cultural events in the city of [[Banyoles]].

== Stage plays ==

In 2011 they debuted with their first full theatre performance in [[Teatre Municipal (Banyoles)|Teatre Municipal de Banyoles]]. ''Júlia?'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elpuntavui.cat/noticia/article/5-cultura/19-cultura/400272-a-partir-dorwell.html |title=A partir d'Orwell |language=catalan |editor=El Punt Avui |date= 21 April 2011}}</ref> with Clàudia Cedó as a director, is an original play inspired in [[1984 (book)|1984]] by [[George Orwell]] that they define as a [[tragicomedy]] about social networks.<ref name="Dossier"/> In 2013 they released ''De petits tots matàvem formigues'' (''We all used to kill ants when we were kids'')<ref>{{cite web |url=http://banyolestv.cat/index.php/noticies/general/cultura/item/1634-el-vol-del-pollastre-estrena-%E2%80%9Cde-petits-tots-mat%C3%A0vem-formigues%E2%80%9D-aquest-cap-de-setmana |title=El vol del Pollastre estrena "De petits tots matàvem formigues", aquest cap de setmana |language=catalan |editor=Banyoles TV |date= 13 November 2013}}</ref> again directed by Clàudia Cedó, in [[Factoria d'Arts Escèniques (Banyoles)|Factoria d'Arts Escèniques]]. This second work, also an original, is a [[Western (genre)|western]] with a touch of [[Film noir]].<ref>{{cite web |title=El Vol del Pollastre i Comediants Kafkiana estrenen a Banyoles |url=http://www.diaridegirona.cat/cultura/2013/11/07/vol-del-pollastre-comediants-kafkiana/642635.html |language=catalan |editor=Diari de Girona |date= 9 November 2013}}</ref> Both works have also been played in [[Girona]]: ''Júlia?'' in [[Centre Cultural la Mercè]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://premsa.gencat.cat/pres_fsvp/AppJava/notapremsavw/detall.do?id=173166 |title=La Taula de Salut Jove de Girona sensibilitza els adolescents a través del teatre sobre els riscos d'addicció en l'ús de les noves tecnologies |language=catalan |editor=Generalitat de Catalunya |date= 10 December 2012}}</ref> and  ''De petits tots matàvem formigues'' in [[Sala La Planeta]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://banyolestv.cat/index.php/noticies/general/cultura/item/2139-%E2%80%9Cde-petits-tots-mat%C3%A0vem-formigues%E2%80%9D-de-la-companyia-el-vol-del-pollastre-s%E2%80%99estrenar%C3%A0-a-girona-aquest-cap-de-setmana |title="De petits tots matàvem formigues", de la companyia El vol del pollastre, s’estrenarà a Girona aquest cap de setmana |language=catalan |editor=Banyoles TV |date= 26 February 2014}}</ref>

== Awards ==
* First prize (Catalunya) for ''De petits tots matàvem formigues''. 11th ''Premios Buero de Teatro Joven''. 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=La companyia banyolina El Vol del Pollastre, premi Buero de Teatre Jove|editor=[[Diari de Girona]]|url=http://www.diaridegirona.cat/cultura/2014/05/23/companyia-banyolina-vol-del-pollastre/670812.html|date=23 May 2014|language=catalan}}</ref><ref name="buero-2014">{{cite web|url=http://estaticos.cocacola.es/bases/fundacion/palmares-premios-autonomicos-2014.pdf|title=Palmarés Premios Buero|editor=Premios Buero|year=2014|language=spanish}}</ref>
* Best set design (Catalunya) for ''De petits tots matàvem formigues''. 11th ''Premios Buero de Teatro Joven''. 2014.<ref name="buero-2014" />

